== Definitions ==

"Protocol" means the Ritual Protocol and its cryptographic design as
described in the official specification document.

"V1 Profile" means the specific set of constants defined in this
implementation that enable interoperability with Ritual Protocol V1:
type tags, domain separator, KDF parameters, and rite datasets.

"Compatible Implementation" means any implementation of the Protocol
that uses the V1 Profile constants and produces identical keys for
identical ritual inputs.

"Commercial Use" means use in a product or service for which you charge
fees, or use in internal business operations of a for-profit entity.

